 due to the fact that the chirp and time-reversed chirp briefly overlap at =
40&nbsp;MHz.</span></p><h2 style=3D"text-align: left"><b>Choosing the right=
 spectrum analyzer for cross-correlation</b></h2><p><span style=3D"font-wei=
ght: 400">Due to the reconfigurability of the Moku:Pro FPGA, as well as its=
 capacity to handle large volumes of data in real time, the Moku:Pro Spectr=
um Analyzer can perform and analyze cross-correlation measurements with enh=
anced precision, flexibility, and efficiency. Whether it is in phase noise =
analysis, time-delay estimation, or signal similarity assessment, the use o=
f Moku:Pro hardware for cross-correlation measurements offers high precisio=
n and versatility essential for advanced research and development applicati=
ons.</span></p><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400">Check out these case stu=
